latestPosts.caption:
EARLY CHECK-IN: Sextantio Le Grotte della Civita 
Checked into possibly the most romantic (most expensive) hotel I’ve been to… ALONE. A cultural preservation project that went on to become a a case study in architecture and design. 😍👏
Designed by Daniele Kihlgren, the property retains the Sassi cave dwellings’ original volumes, textures, and materials. His mission to revive abandoned Italian villages through the concept of ‘Albergo Diffuso’, integrating hospitality with heritage. Interiors are deliberately sparse, lime-washed stone, monastic furnishings, and raw finishes allowing the ancient structure to lead the narrative. Modern comforts exist quietly: Philippe Starck bathtubs, radiant heating beneath original floors, and candlelit ambiance that respects the site’s medieval soul. A design philosophy rooted not in reinvention, but radical restraint. 😮‍💨✨

I loved how the design didn’t compete with the history. It just let it BREATHE. A hotel that feels more like time travel with underfloor heating.
Me and the stone walls had deep conversations about texture, silence, and emotional availability, so I’d say yes to solo travelling here. 🫶😍
.
Trip curated by @travalongjourneys 🙌
.
#EarlyCheckIn #interiordesign #hoteldesign #luxuryhotels #interiors #hotels #travel #matera #italy #siddhikarwa

#ELLECulture: “I didn’t have a fashion background or any exposure to pop culture growing up,” admits lifestyle content creator and designer Siddhi Karwa (@siddhikarwaa ). Moving to Mumbai for advertising studies was a cultural whirlwind, but Karwa was instantly captivated by the city’s vibrant fashion scene. At 18, a serendipitous encounter with Balaji Telefilms, a major force in Indian television and film, changed everything. An acting stint with them emboldened her to embrace new challenges and chart a bold new path. Head to the 🔗 in the bio to read more about her creative journey.

My First COVER! 😍🧿✨🥺
My first ever project, also my beautiful house gracing the digital cover of @goodhomesmagazine . Came to me as a total surprise and I couldn’t process it for the longest. People who know me, know how precious this is to me. Jumping places and shifting careers has been the most challenging thing lately, but I’m so  ecstatic to see where this journey takes me and I can’t wait to dive in deeper, it has only begun. 🧿
Special thanks to @debarati_roy who’s constantly shown immense support and who’s truly been there when no one was. You know how special this is for me. And thank you to @vanitagarora who’s beautifully penned this down and for giving me the opportunity. Lastly, @thelazyinsomniac and @ayesymmetrical who made my work look even better and justified my aesthetic truly with these photos. Couldn’t have asked anyone else to shoot my space. ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
I turned 30 yesterday and honestly? It wasn’t the life I pictured.
It is so much more richer and beautiful than I imagined! 
I became the passenger princess on road trips that felt like therapy.
I moved through cities that felt like soulmates.
I designed homes and dreamt up wild ideas.
I built deep friendships, the kind that feel like lifelong commitment without rings.
I was privileged to feel heartaches and love over and over again. 
I cried on planes and danced in bathrooms alone and rebuilt myself more than once.

My milestones didn’t come with trophies.
They came in the form of people, places, late-night introspection, solo flights, chaotic detours, and quiet moments where I realized I’m actually pretty proud of this life.

So no, it’s not the life I planned by 30.
But it’s full of meaning and memories I wouldn’t trade for anyone else’s checklist.

Here’s to a new decade , with more heart, more honesty, and maybe still no car! 😌

latestPosts.caption:
Episode 3:Here’s how I DESIGNED MY DREAM BATHROOM! 🥹😍😮‍💨
.
This series was never intended to show a BEFORE & AFTER of a space but to actually take you through my process of thought, concept, material and technicalities involved to get there. I always wanted an open bathroom, since I live alone, I don’t have to share my bedroom with anyone so it was quite doable plus I wanted my obsession of waking up in a hotel room come alive, and I guess it did! 🥹

Obviously things you need to keep in mind while doing an open bathroom layout: 

1. Permissions are the most important, from your builder. Consult an architect/designer for your External RCC walls before breaking. 
	2.	Make your layout work for your lifestyle. You don’t need to follow the textbook.
	3.	Zone it out. Wet zone, dry zone, WC zone. It’s like choreography. Everyone needs their mark.
	4.	Plumbing is your boss. Check where the pipes go before dreaming big or prepare for heartbreak.
	5.	Slopes & drainage matter. Water is sneaky. Slope it right or regret it daily.
	6.	Waterproofing is not aesthetic but it’s crucial. Ask your contractor twice. 
	7.	Make the boring bits beautiful. Niches, ledges, mirrors, these aren’t just cute, they hide chaos.
	8.	Open-plan bathrooms? Sexy. But only if you create privacy within it.
	9.	Ventilation isn’t a luxury, it’s your mold insurance.
	10.	Keep it personal. Civil work is a mess, but it’s the one time you get to redesign your life behind the walls.
.
Bathrooms are not just functional spaces anymore. They’ve evolved from ‘get in, get out’ to ‘this is therapy corner, and my creative space.’ So be fearless and innovative before you design your next bathroom. 
.
